Germany's new warship postponed once again
The German Navy's newest frigate was supposed to be delivered in 2014 to replace the old Cold War-era warships, but won't arrive until at least next year due to faulty systems and the increasing cost, local media reported.
The commissioning of the Rheinland-Pfalz, the lead ship of the Baden-Wuerttemberg-class flamboyant frigates, has been delayed until the first half of 2019, a military spokesman told Die Zeit.
The ship was due to be commissioned into the Navy in 2014, but problems after delivery affected the fate of this ambitious project.
The four Baden-Württemberg-class ships, which the Navy ordered in 2007, will replace the old Bremen-class frigates.
